# External links (`target="_blank"`)

Every link that opens in a new tab must include `rel="noopener noreferrer"` to prevent tabnabbing and limit referrer leakage.

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<a href="https://example.com" target="_blank">Example</a>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<a href="https://example.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Example</a>
```

```javascript
// ❌ BAD
anchor.setAttribute("target", "_blank")

// ✅ GOOD
anchor.setAttribute("target", "_blank")
anchor.setAttribute("rel", "noopener noreferrer")
```

**CMS markdown** (`src/pages/**/*-cms.md` via `sanitizeHtml`) gets `rel` at render — no need to duplicate in source.

**Verify:** run `npm run check:target-blank` (full repo) before release. Pre-commit runs `--warn --staged` on changed files only.
